# GOAL.PRD

## Aryavrat Studio Portal (SaaS-Style Agency System)

---

# 1. PRODUCT GOAL

Build a premium SaaS-style agency platform where:

* Clients can order services
* Managers can manage projects
* Approved work automatically appears in the public portfolio

The system must feel structured, premium, and operational — not like a freelancer website.

Timeline target: Fast MVP foundation (buildable within 1–2 focused sessions).

---

# 2. PRODUCT POSITIONING

Product Name (Internal): Aryavrat Studio Portal
Public Framing: "Private Client Workspace"

This is not:

* A marketplace
* A gig platform
* An AI tool

This is:

* A structured studio system
* A client operations dashboard
* A long-term partnership platform

---

# 3. CORE USER TYPES

## 3.1 Client

Can:

* Create new service orders
* Track order status
* View deliverables
* Request revisions
* Approve completed work
* View order history

## 3.2 Admin (Manager)

Can:

* View all projects
* Change project status
* Upload deliverables
* Toggle "Show in Portfolio"
* Add project metrics (CTR, growth, etc.)

---

# 4. CORE FEATURES (MVP)

## 4.1 Public Website Layer

Pages:

* Home
* Services
* Work (auto-fed from approved projects)
* About
* Login

Work page auto-displays:
Projects where:

* status = "Completed"
* show_in_portfolio = true

---

## 4.2 Client Dashboard

Route: /dashboard

Features:

* Overview panel
* New Order form
* Orders list (status-based)
* Project detail view (modal or page)
* Comment thread
* Approve & Close button

Statuses:

* Pending Review
* In Progress
* Delivered
* Revision Requested
* Approved
* Completed

---

## 4.3 Admin Panel

Route: /admin

Features:

* All projects table
* Status change control
* Deliverable upload
* Portfolio toggle switch
* Project metrics input

Auto-portfolio logic:
When:

* status = Completed
* show_in_portfolio = true

Then:

* Project appears on /work page

---

# 5. DATA MODEL (MVP)

## users

* id
* name
* email
* role (client/admin)
* created_at

## projects

* id
* user_id
* title
* description
* service_type
* status
* deadline
* deliverable_url
* show_in_portfolio (boolean)
* created_at

## comments

* id
* project_id
* user_id
* message
* created_at

---

# 6. TECH STACK

Frontend:

* Next.js 14 (App Router)
* TailwindCSS
* Lucide Icons

Backend:

* Supabase (Auth + DB + Storage)

Deployment:

* Vercel

---

# 7. DESIGN SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

Theme:

* Dark neutral base (#111 or similar)
* Elevated dark cards (#1a1a1a range)
* Warm accent (muted gold / sand tone)

Strictly avoid:

* Blue
* Purple
* Neon gradients
* AI-style glow aesthetics

UI Feel:

* Premium SaaS dashboard
* Glassmorphism navbar
* Sidebar layout (dashboard)
* Soft rounded corners (not bubbly)
* Large spacing
* No emojis

Icons:

* Lucide only

---

# 8. RESPONSIVENESS

Desktop:

* Sidebar layout
* Floating glass navbar

Tablet:

* Compact sidebar
* Scaled typography

Mobile:

* Bottom dock navigation
* Stacked layout
* Bottom-sheet modals
* No horizontal scroll

---

# 9. SUCCESS CRITERIA

MVP is successful if:

* Client can create order
* Admin can update status
* Client can approve project
* Approved project automatically appears on Work page
* UI feels premium and operational

---

# 10. LONG-TERM EXPANSION (NOT MVP)

* Notifications
* Client billing system
* Subscription retainers
* Team roles
* Analytics dashboard

